com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.annotations

Annotation Type Command


  • @Target(value=METHOD)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Command
    Methods annotated with Command will be registered as a command at startup.

    Therefore the method must be declared inside a class that is annotated with CommandController. Furthermore the method signature has to meet the following conditions:

    • public access modifier and no return type
    • First parameter must be of type CommandEvent
    • Remaining parameters must either be parsable by the ArgumentParser or be a String array
    • Parameter options defined by Optional and by Concat must be valid
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Kaktushose
    See Also:
    CommandController, CommandEvent, ArgumentParser, Concat, Optional
